<HEADLINE>
<P>
QUE PASA?; 
</P>
<P>
PEOPLE AND EVENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By EDWARD J. BOYER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
* Attorney John Huerta has joined Los Angeles' Western Center on Law and 
Poverty as a specialist in land use and housing law, and he has also been named 
to the city's new Affordable Housing Commission. 
</P>
<P>
"I enjoy helping poor people, the people who don't have the means to assert 
their rights," said Huerta, once an attorney for the Mexican American Legal 
Defense and Educational Fund. "In today's legal market, people with low and 
moderate income cannot afford attorneys," he said. Huerta said his goal on the 
commission "is to make more affordable housing available in Los Angeles for 
low-income and moderate-income individuals -- not just in ghetto areas." EDWARD 
J. BOYER 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, COLOR, John Huerta 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
<TYPE>
<P>
Appointment 
</P>
