<P>
SOUTH BAY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MAN IS SHOT, KILLED NEAR ATHENS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Los Angeles man who was walking along a sidewalk in an unincorporated area 
near Athens was fatally wounded Tuesday night when he was shot numerous times 
in the back, sheriff's officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Deputy Gabe Ramirez of the Sheriff's Information Bureau said Charles Sweed, 28, 
was pronounced dead at 10:30 p.m at Martin Luther King Jr. 
</P>
<P>
-Drew Medical Center. Sweed had just left a house he was visiting in the 11200 
block of South New Hampshire Avenue about 9 p.m. when he was attacked by an 
unknown assailant, sheriff's officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Ramirez said the motive for the slaying was unknown, and no arrests had been 
made as of Wednesday afternoon. Homicide detectives from the Lennox substation 
were investigating. 
</P>
</TEXT>
