<HEADLINE>
<P>
PROPOSAL TO BAN LEAF BLOWERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I commend you for acknowledging the negative impacts of leaf blowers ("It's 
Time to Throttle Leaf Blowers," On California, by Robert A. Jones, Nov. 27). 
Noise pollution is only one impact associated with leaf blowers that I have 
coined the "mechanical devices from hell." 
</P>
<P>
Leaf blowers also are the culprits of two other sources of air pollution. Their 
two-cycle motors belch out blue smoke via the oil/gas mixture fuel. During the 
deceptive process of cleaning an area they create substantial volumes of dust 
that become airborne only to lodge in our respiratory systems. 
</P>
<P>
Indian Wells has received a positive response to our recently enacted ordinance 
banning their use. I can only hope that other cities follow this positive and 
environmentally sound action. 
</P>
<P>
PHILIP A. MANUELL 
</P>
<P>
City Councilman, Indian Wells 
</P>
</TEXT>
