WEEKDAY UPDATE; 
</P>
<P>
RAMS; 
</P>
<P>
COX, JOHNSON LISTED AS QUESTIONABLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIM KAWAKAMI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Injury Update: Wide receiver Aaron Cox and tight end Damone Johnson, both of 
whom missed last Sunday's 38-23 victory over the Browns in Cleveland, are 
listed as questionable for this Sunday because of sore hamstrings; cornerback 
Bobby Humphery is probable despite a calf injury. All three practiced 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Coach John Robinson agreed with New York Giant Coach Bill Parcells' 
controversial decision to bypass a field goal and go for the touchdown on 
fourth and goal while trailing the San Francisco 49ers, 7-3, Monday night. The 
Giants failed on the try and lost by the same score. 
</P>
<P>
"I'd have gone for it," Robinson said without hesitation. "If you kick the 
field goal, the 49ers get the ball at the 30 probably, 25 or 30. Which is far 
different than at the nine. . . . You may never get the ball back. My thought 
was, you aren't ever going to get down there again. I would've gone for it. And 
the way it turned out, I would've been wrong." TIM KAWAKAMI 
</P>
</TEXT>
