<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL REPORT; 
</P>
<P>
WEEKDAY UPDATE; 
</P>
<P>
CHARGERS; 
</P>
<P>
CORNERBACK LILLY SIGNED, GOSS WAIVED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Chargers on Wednesday signed cornerback Sammy Lilly and waived linebacker 
Antonio Goss, who was signed Nov. 21 when linebacker Richard Brown was put on 
injured reserve. 
</P>
<P>
Lilly (5-9, 175) was selected in the eighth round of the 1988 draft by the New 
York Giants. After spending his rookie season on injured reserve because of a 
knee injury, he joined the Philadelphia Eagles in 1989 and played 15 games. 
</P>
<P>
This season, he was on the Eagles' roster for the first 10 games, playing in 
seven. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
