<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Outside hitter Caren Kemner and setter Javier Gaspar on Wednesday night were 
named Most Valuable Players of their respective teams for 1991 at the U.S. 
Volleyball awards banquet at a Mission Valley hotel. 
</P>
<P>
Kemner played in Europe for much of 1990, but came back to the national team to 
lead it to a bronze medal in both the Goodwill Games and the World 
Championships in China. 
</P>
<P>
Gaspar was a steadying force during a difficult year that saw head coach Bill 
Neville resign. 
</P>
<P>
TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
Five San Diego area players on Wednesday advanced to the second round of the 
8th Rancho Bernardo Inn Grand Prix Masters Tennis Championships. 
</P>
<P>
In Men's 60, Harry Brown of San Diego defeated John Bennett of Sherman Oaks, 
6-4, 6-4. 
</P>
<P>
In Men's 65, Stan Potts of San Diego put down Clare Hoke of Claremont, 6-3, 
7-5, and Bob Seymour of Del Mar got by Fran Jones of La Quinta, 6-4, 6-4. 
</P>
<P>
In Men's 80, Bill Conel of Oceanside eased past Ron Brandon of Anaheim, 6-0, 
6-3 and in Women's 60 Virginia glass of San Diego defeated Piyachart Hussey of 
Laguna Hills, 6-0, 4-6, 6-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
