<TEXT>
<P>
Robert A. Rivero has been appointed partner-in-charge of the audit practice for 
the Los Angeles office of the accounting firm KPMG Peat Marwick. He succeeds 
Clarence T. Schmitz, who was recently named managing partner of the Los Angeles 
office. Rivero joins the Los Angeles office after five years at Peat Marwick's 
Miami office, where he served as audit partner-in-charge. 
