<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AIDS Show Will Air: The AIDS episode of "Lifestories" that NBC had been 
reluctant to air will finally be shown Dec. 18 at 10 p.m., the network said 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
The program, which deals frankly with AIDS, gay men and television's fears of 
dealing with the disease, had previously been scheduled to air on Dec. 2 in the 
series' regular early evening time slot. But the network yanked it, saying the 
subject matter was inappropriate for an 8 p.m. broadcast. Production on 
"Lifestories" itself has been shut down because of low ratings. CLAUDIA PUIG 
</P>
</TEXT>
