Westwood Club Luminarias: (Dec. 24, 6 p.m., West Bernardo Drive and Rancho 
Bernardo Road, Rancho Bernardo). Boy Scout Troop 681, led by Eldon Jennings, 
will sell paper bags with candles set in sand to about 2,000 homeowners in the 
Westwood Club area of Rancho Bernardo. Community volunteers help prepare the 
luminarias for sale. Residents light the 44,000 candles Dec. 24. The display 
can be viewed by driving or strolling down streets in the area. Drivers are 
asked to use parking lights during the display, which has been an event for 
about 20 years. 
