<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRIMINAL, NOT A HUNTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Times' article "Police Seek Man Who Killed Doe With a Crossbow" refers to 
the sick individual who committed this horrendous crime as a "hunter." 
</P>
<P>
This man does not fit the definition of a hunter, a man or woman who enjoys 
nature and all that it has to offer. Ninety-nine percent of hunters respect and 
abide by the rules and regulations that govern the sport. 
</P>
<P>
The Times is helping feed the anti-hunting fire, ensuring that the decent men 
and women who enjoy this noble sport are stripped of their privilege to do so. 
</P>
<P>
AL SANCHEZ 
</P>
<P>
Palmdale 
</P>
</TEXT>
