<P>
MCI Tells of 900 Service Rules: The nation's second-largest long-distance 
company announced guidelines designed to help protect customers from misleading 
or fraudulent services on 900-telephone numbers, which it plans to start 
offering nationwide on Jan. 1. The company said the consumer safeguards will 
include a $4 cap on each call to child-oriented 900 services; pre-screening of 
programs and advertising and a requirement that adult services be placed on a 
single prefix, when available, to facilitate blocking requests by customers. 
