<TEXT>
<P>
Steinberg Concern Holds 2% Stake in UAL: New York investor Saul P. Steinberg, 
once a major holder of the stock of UAL Corp., has again bought into the parent 
company of United Airlines, according to documents. A subsidiary of a Steinberg 
family-controlled concern, Reliance Group Holdings Inc., disclosed in a filing 
with the Securities and Exchange Commission that it has purchased 451,000 
shares of UAL common stock. 
</P>
<P>
The filing, covering the quarter ending Sept. 30, disclosed that the subsidiary 
-- Reliance Financial Services Corp. -- paid more than $43.9 million for the 
shares. But the document is not required disclose exactly where or when the 
purchases were made. "As a policy, we don't comment on our investment," said 
Brian Martin, a spokesman for New York-based Reliance. In Chicago, UAL 
spokesman Joe Hopkins also declined to comment. 
</P>
