<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEARS TO FREEZE PAY OF SALARIED EMPLOYEES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHICAGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sears, Roebuck &amp; Co., the nation's No. 1 department store chain, said 
Wednesday that it has told its salaried staff members that their pay next year 
will be frozen at present levels. 
</P>
<P>
The freeze, which the company said will be reviewed as conditions warrant, is 
part of a companywide cost-reduction program and affects about 20,000 
employees. 
</P>
<P>
Sears' sales have been under pressure in recent months. The company said in 
October that its third-quarter earnings fell to 53 cents a share, down from 75 
cents. 
</P>
