<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: EL MONTE; 
</P>
<P>
BAN ON SCAVENGING DEFEATED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Who has the right to the bottles and cans residents place at the curb for 
recycling? 
</P>
<P>
The City Council last week voted down and sent back to the city attorney for 
revision an ordinance that would have prohibited trash scavenging. 
</P>
<P>
Councilwoman Patricia Wallach, who earlier backed the measure, spoke against it 
last week. She said some people make a living scavenging. But some residents 
said the scavengers break bottles and invade their privacy. 
</P>
<P>
The measure, requested by Webster Disposal Co., which contracts with the city 
for trash pickup and recycling, would have allowed scavenging only with the 
property owner's permission. 
</P>
</TEXT>
