<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: LA VERNE; 
</P>
<P>
LITTLE SUPPORT FOR RAIL PLAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council on Monday showed little enthusiasm for building a rail station 
in La Verne as part of the planned San Bernardino-to-Los Angeles commuter line. 
</P>
<P>
The council voted 3 to 2 to allow Councilman Craig H. Walters to explore the 
possibility if he wished, but it forbade city staff members to spend any time 
on the project. 
</P>
<P>
Mayor Jon Harry Blickenstaff and Mayor Pro Tem Thomas R. Harvey said it would 
cost the city too much to build and maintain such a station. 
</P>
<P>
However, council members Walters and Patrick J. Gatti stressed the importance 
of accessible transportation. 
</P>
<P>
Asst. City Manager Jeffry Allred said a station would not benefit the city's 
budget and could hurt it by taking commercial land off the tax rolls. However, 
he suggested that if the city decides it wants a station, officials could work 
with neighboring San Dimas to find possible sites along Arrow Highway. 
</P>
</TEXT>
