<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: AZUSA; 
</P>
<P>
QUARRY'S PERMIT RENEWED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Azusa Rock Co. will be able to continue rock mining at its Fish Canyon Road 
quarry, the City Council decided Monday, over the objections of several 
residents. 
</P>
<P>
The council voted 3 to 2 to renew the quarry's permit, saying it has complied 
with all city conditions. 
</P>
<P>
However, the council required the company to report to the city monthly on its 
efforts to restore parts of the mountain that are not being mined. The council 
also required the company to install sound-absorbing barriers around its 
rock-crushing equipment. 
</P>
<P>
The council decision followed a public hearing in which several residents said 
the quarry was a nuisance, creating dust in the air and scarring the 
mountainside. 
</P>
<P>
Councilman Stephen J. Alexander and Mayor Eugene F. Moses voted against the 
permit. "We have a mountain and it is being destroyed," Alexander said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
