<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN CLEMENTE; 
</P>
<P>
COUNCIL HANDS THE GAVEL TO DIEHL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Councilman Scott Diehl was unanimously elected mayor Wednesday at City Hall. 
</P>
<P>
Diehl, 40, a local veterinarian, was elected to a four-year council term in 
1988 and previously served a four-year from 1982 to 1986. 
</P>
<P>
His mayoral term is for one year. 
</P>
<P>
Returning Councilman Thomas Lorch and two new council members also took office 
at inaugural ceremonies Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Lorch, a retired aerospace engineer, returned for his second, consecutive 
four-year term on the council. 
</P>
<P>
Also sworn-in on Wednesday were Councilman Joseph Anderson, 48, a businessman 
and the top vote-getter in the Nov. 6 election, and Councilman Truman Benedict, 
67, a retired teacher and former superintendent of the Capistrano Unified 
School District. Anderson also was named mayor pro tem. 
</P>
<P>
Outgoing Mayor Candace Haggard, a county librarian, has two years remaining in 
her council term. Outgoing Councilman Brian J. Rice, 43, failed to win 
reelection, and outgoing Councilwoman Holly Veale chose not to seek reelection. 
</P>
</TEXT>
