<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FULLERTON; 
</P>
<P>
RATIONAL THERAPY AUTHOR IN SEMINAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Noted psychotherapist and educator Albert Ellis will hold a special seminar 
Sunday at Cal State Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
Ellis, who gained fame in the early 1960s for his rational approach to therapy, 
will hold a seven-hour seminar in the Ruby Gerontology Center on the campus at 
State College Boulevard and Nutwood Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
Ellis, 77, has written more than 50 books, including "Sex Without Guilt" and 
"How to Stubbornly Refuse to Make Yourself Miserable About Anything -- Yes 
Anything!" He holds a doctorate in clinical psychology from Columbia University 
and has been executive director of the Institute for Rational-Emotive Therapy 
in New York City since 1959. 
</P>
<P>
Ellis' seminar is being sponsored by the university's Psychology Department 
Assn. An admission fee of $25 includes lunch. For tickets or information, call 
(714) 773-3514. 
</P>
</TEXT>
