<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: RETAIL / TOURISM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Chris Woodyard; Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A New Look: The Doubletree Hotel in Orange is getting a face-lift. 
</P>
<P>
Each of the bathrooms in the 461-room hotel will be renovated at a cost of 
$620,000. And starting in February, the next phase of the project will revamp 
the hotel's junior and grand ballrooms at a cost of $1.3 million. 
</P>
<P>
Michelle Manire, the hotel's general manager, promises that guests won't have 
to listen to the pounding of hammers and screech of buzz saws. 
</P>
<P>
"Careful scheduling ensures our guests won't even be aware that the work is 
being done," she said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
HOTELS -- ORANGE COUNTY; REMODELING 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
