<HEADLINE>
<P>
GISH BIOMEDICAL STOCK OFF 20% 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SANTA ANA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gish Biomedical Inc.'s stock fell 20% Wednesday after the manufacturer of 
disposable cardiovascular products said sales for its second quarter ending 
Dec. 31 would be "closer to $5 million rather than the $5.5 million projected 
by analysts." 
</P>
<P>
Gish's stock, which is traded over-the-counter, closed at $9.875 a share, down 
$2.50. 
</P>
<P>
The company said it was lowering the sales projection for the quarter because 
its distributors are reducing their product inventories in preparation for a 
weakening economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
