<HEADLINE>
<P>
* ANTONIO DACOSTA; PORTUGUESE PAINTER, ART CRITIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Antonio Dacosta, 76, an artist and art critic who introduced surrealism to 
Portugal and became one of the country's leading painters. 
</P>
<P>
Dacosta was inspired by French and Spanish surrealists, especially the Spanish 
artist Salvador Dali, and held the first surrealist exhibition in Portugal in 
1940. In 1949, he abandoned painting to work as a journalist and art critic in 
Paris for Portuguese and Brazilian newspapers. Dacosta returned to painting in 
1975. His early works show a dramatic, fluid use of forms and colors. Later 
works are more abstract with gentler color use, influenced by the rural 
landscapes of the Azores. On Sunday in Paris of unreported causes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
