WESTSIDE DIGEST: CULVER CITY; 
</P>
<P>
CITY HALL PROJECT LIAISON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has designated Gary Audet, director of municipal services, to 
be the staff project manager for the design development phase of the 
construction of the new city hall. 
</P>
<P>
Audet will act as the liaison among the project's architect, CHCG Inc.; the 
construction manager, Jones Construction Management, and the city. 
</P>
<P>
His duties will include coordinating decisions and recommendations by other 
city staff for the building design during the next three years. 
</P>
<P>
The architect is scheduled to present preliminary plans for the city hall 
complex to the council in two weeks. The plans will show basic floor plans and 
describe overall building functions. It will be the job of Audet and others to 
work out office layouts, select many of the finishing materials and decide on 
aesthetic details. 
</P>
<P>
A City Hall Advisory Team composed of Mayor Steven Gourley, City Councilman 
Mike Balkman and other key department heads will also help make design 
decisions. 
</P>
