<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY DIGEST: LONG BEACH; 
</P>
<P>
TRANSIT BOARD TO CONSIDER RAISING BUS FARE TO 75 CENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Long Beach Transit's directors are scheduled to raise bus fares for the first 
time when they meet Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Officials said the increase is necessary in part to make up for a staggering 
increase in the cost of fuel. 
</P>
<P>
Adults would pay 75 cents, an increase of 15 cents. Student fares would 
increase 10 cents to 50 cents, and senior citizens would pay 35 cents, an 
increase of 5 cents. 
</P>
<P>
Transit officials say the cost of diesel fuel has more than doubled to nearly 
$1.10 a gallon. City buses use about 2 million gallons of fuel a year. "At the 
current rate, our fuel costs are going to increase by over $1 million this 
year," General Manager Laurence Jackson said. 
</P>
