</P>
<P>
GRAND MET PROFITS SURGE 25% 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
British food and beverages group Grand Metropolitan PLC said today its profits 
surged 25% last year, helped by a turnaround at its Burger King fast food 
division. 
</P>
<P>
Pretax profits for the year ended Sept. 30 jumped to 919 million pounds ($1.76 
billion) from 732 million pounds ($1.41 billion). Revenues edged up to 9.39 
billion pounds ($18.12 billion) from 9.30 billion pounds ($17.95 billion). 
</P>
<P>
Burger King, acquired as part of the $5.8-billion takeover of Minneapolis-based 
Pillsbury Co. two years ago, doubled its operating profits, to 125 million 
pounds ($249 million) from 76 million pounds ($150 million). 
</P>
<P>
Burger King's weak performance had been considered the key factor behind 
Pillsbury's takeover, and skeptics believed it might also undermine Grand Met. 
</P>
</TEXT>
