<P>
LAKERS WAIVE SWINGMAN BROWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Lakers announced today that they have waived swingman Tony Brown. 
</P>
<P>
Brown, a 6-6 five-year NBA veteran, was placed on the injured list by the 
Lakers Nov. 30 because of a bruised right knee cap. He appeared in seven games 
this season, averaging 3.9 minutes per appearance. 
</P>
