<TEXT>
<P>
Rookie power forward Derrick Coleman of the New Jersey Nets will miss Friday 
night's game against the Phoenix Suns because of an ankle injury, a team 
spokesman said. Coleman could be back in uniform for next week's games against 
Charlotte and Atlanta despite an initially gloomy prognosis, Nets spokesman 
John Mertz said. On Wednesday, Coach Bill Fitch said Coleman could be out up to 
10 days because of a sprained ankle. 
</P>
