<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHORT TAKES; 
</P>
<P>
BOSTON SYMPHONY TO GO ON TOUR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BOSTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Boston Symphony Orchestra will tour the United States next spring and 
perform in Europe late in the summer, conductor Seiji Ozawa said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
The U.S. tour, scheduled for April 22-May 3, will be the orchestra's first 
transcontinental tour since 1981. 
</P>
<P>
The U.S. tour will include performances in Pittsburgh, Toronto, Chicago, New 
York, Cleveland, Los Angeles, San Francisco and Tempe, Ariz. 
</P>
<P>
The European tour, running from Aug. 24 to Sept. 8, includes stops in Athens; 
Salzburg, Austria; Munich, Stuttgart and Frankfurt, Germany; Paris and London. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief; Wire 
</P>
